<p>They intended to run a picture that made him look ordinary, but they ended up making him look like the latest pop star Rolling Stone wants you to pay attention to.</p>
<p>Part of this was the photo selection - I don't think Rolling Stone really gets "ordinary" - and part of it is the cultural significance that the Rolling Stone cover carries. When you see a picture that looks like that on Rolling Stone's cover, that's almost always what they're doing.</p>
